Conditions of Application: By applying to Duke, you agree to be bound by our Community Standard and you are consenting to the conditions listed below. The only valid notification of an admissions decision is the formal letter of admission from the Dean of Undergraduate Admissions.Duke University may discontinue your application, withdraw an offer of admission, or revoke your enrollment at any time if you do not meet these conditions. The integrity of your applicationYou agree that all the information in your application is true and accurate, including your citizenship or U.S. visa status. You agree that your application reflects your own work, and that all application materials submitted by you were not created by another person or by a generative artificial intelligence process.Applying Early Decision at Duke or elsewhere If you apply to Duke under our Early Decision program you agree to fully abide by the terms of our Early Decision agreement. You agree to abide by the conditions of application of other universities you are applying to. You agree to immediately withdraw your application to Duke if you are accepted at another college or university under their binding Early Decision program. Personal behavior and integrityYou agree not to act in a manner that calls into question your honesty, integrity, or character. Authorization and Personal data collectionYou authorize discussion of your candidacy by the Admissions Office with appropriate faculty and staff of all educational institutions you have attended as well as any other institutions where you have worked, served, lived or volunteered in the last four years; You understand and agree that by submitting an application for admission, the personal data included with your application will be collected by Duke, or on its behalf, during the admissions process; and that this data will be used for the primary purposes of considering your application for admission to Duke, providing you with information regarding engagement opportunities, evaluating your eligibility for financial aid, responding to records requests and, if you are admitted, facilitating your education. You agree that your data may be shared internally with Duke departments, or with third parties, to help achieve these goals and to comply with legal obligations. We do not consider information on criminal history during our initial round of admission application reviews. Only upon selecting a pool of admitted candidates do we learn whether you have reported a criminal history, at which point we will offer you an opportunity to explain the circumstances. With this approach, information on misdemeanor or felony convictions can inform, but not determine, admission decisions. It ensures that applicants are evaluated based on their academic profile, extracurricular pursuits and potential fit - not criminal history - and enables us to continue to review this potentially important information. Ultimately, our goal is to make an informed decision about what is best for you and best for Brown. *
